Nairobi, Kenya: Police on patrol recover 3 pistols and 51 rounds of ammunition from undeveloped plot in Karen, Nairobi, following a tip off from the public. Police raided the area where they met three suspected gangsters who however managed to escape. The gangsters fired at them as they escaped on foot dropping house breaking weapons. Karen OCPD Cunningham Suiyanka has called on area residents to remain vigilant and report any suspicious activities in the area, even as a manhunt has ensued to capture the suspects. READ MORE Police shoot dead four suspects along Likoni Road, Nairobi City mall borrows design elements from old Europe Kibaki jets back to the country after treatment in South Africa